article.description: — Maciej Bender had a career-high 21 points and Mercer beat Kennesaw State 81-71 on Tuesday.
article.headline: Bender scores 21 to lead Mercer past Kennesaw State 81-71
article.linkText: Bender scores 21 to lead Mercer past Kennesaw State 81-71
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- — Maciej Bender had a career-high 21 points and Mercer beat Kennesaw State 81-71 on Tuesday. Ross Cummings had 15 points for Mercer (7-1), Leon Ayers III added 15 points and Felipe Haase had 11 points, 10 rebounds and five assists. Spencer Rodgers had 20 points for the Owls (3-5). Terrell Burden added 17 points. Chris Youngblood had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
